flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Detection of supplier disruption signals, large input cost movement, or upcoming high-impact promotional window from monitoring feeds or scheduled scans.]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers - Ingest N-tier registry and operational signals into the subject area and canonical supplier graph]
  N1 --> N2[Stream: STREAMS - Normalize and enrich supplier data; compute node-level risk and capacity metrics]
  N2 --> N3{Agent: Agent Team + Cortex (Agentic AI) - Execute agentic digital-twin stress tests across scenarios (cost spikes, promo surge, transport outage) and rank intervention candidates}
  N3 -->|Primary| N4[PB: Process Builder + Remote Functions + CWB Lifecycle - Orchestrate chosen interventions: trigger Kinaxis expedite, queue S4 contract adjustments via Remote Functions, and create CWB Lifecycle tasks for approvals]
  N4 --> N5[UI: UI Screens (dashboard, report) + CWB Lifecycle - Surface recommended actions and scenario outcomes to planners and procurement via dashboards and CWB; collect decisions/overrides]
  N5 --> N6[PB: Subject Areas + Cortex Monitoring - Monitor execution outcome and close the loop into subject areas for continuous learning and model refinement]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Targeted interventions on high-impact N-tier nodes reduce expected service disruption, preserve planned revenue and margins, limit emergency expediting costs, and maintain service levels while minimizing working capital and EBITDA erosion.]
  N3 -->|Low confidence in supplier data or in...| B1[Process Builder routes to data enrichment subprocess (DDM/Crawlers) and flags manual verification via Agent Team; suspend automated high-impact actions]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Delay or limit automated interventions until data fidelity is restored; create a prioritized data acquisition backlog]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|High-impact disruption but estimated ...| B2[Agent Team generates alternative lower-cost continuity plans; create CWB Lifecycle approvals for executive sign-off and optional contract renegotiation via Remote Functions]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Avoid uncontrolled spend; escalate for human decision with clear cost/benefit tradeoffs]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N3 -->|Multiple simultaneous N-tier failures...| B3[Agentic pipeline runs prioritized Monte Carlo-style stress matrix; Process Builder restricts actions to highest ROI nodes and surfaces remaining risks for manual planning]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Focused, resource-constrained interventions preserve most critical service levels while documenting residual risk]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]